<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in the track of someone • on the track of someone</xh5><p> <i>in the track of someone—</i>following the actual route taken by a person: From here I rushed straight to the Senate, right <u>in the track of</u> this man.</p><p> <i>on the track of someone—</i>in pursuit of smb. (in order to capture): The law commands that the police should always be <u>on the track of</u> criminals.</p> </entry>
